    methodology: 'Ranked on five criteria: pedagogical quality (does the AI improve learning outcomes vs just save time), ease-of-use for non-technical teachers, privacy and student-data safety, free-tier sufficiency for teachers paying out of pocket, and integration with existing classroom tools (Google Classroom, Canvas, Schoology). Each tool was evaluated against real teacher workflows over a 30-day period.',
